notesStmt.note: Title from title page (p. iii), decorated with pen-and-ink title border.
See also UPenn Ms. Codex 458 and Ms. Codex 459.

msContents.summary: Contains 24 satires and 13 sonnets, 2 satires and 10 sonnets marked "inedite" by a former owner (p. 269-270). Dotti's Rime were published in 1689 and his Satire in 1757, 1790, and 1807; no attempt has been made to ascertain whether the supposedly unpublished poems are actually "inedite," or are known in other mss.

supportDesc.extent: 138 leaves : 233 x 168 (176 x 60) mm. bound to 244 x 180 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 138 + i (contemporary paper); [iv] 1-56, 61-270, [ii]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

origin.p: Written in Italy, possibly in the second half of the 18th century.
